tags.name: Camp Downes
tags.note: According to http://pro8.pnp.gov.ph/index.php?option=com_content&view=category&layout=blog&id=52&Itemid=73 , Camp Downes is names after "Pvt. Jorge Downes, a US Army soldier of 24th Infantry Regiment who was killed in action sometime in 1901 ... [cont'd]
tags.note_2: ... at Brgy Mahayay [...] against a fanatical group [...]. A Pulahan chieftain named Faustino Ablan was also killed [...] during said bloody battle." Note that Faustino Abl*e*n was captured on June 11, 1907 only - see "Faustino Ablen Street" in this city.
